@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<p>Effective Date: @DateTime.Now.ToString("MMMM dd, yyyy")</p>

<h2>Introduction</h2>
<p>
    Welcome to Shift Handover, a system operated as part of Bahrain Airport Services (BAS) Airport Company.
    This platform is designed to streamline shift management, incident reporting, and workforce tracking within our operations.
    Protecting your personal information and ensuring transparency is a priority for us.
</p>

<h2>Information We Collect</h2>
<p>We may collect and store the following information:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Personal details such as full name, email address, phone number, and department.</li>
    <li>System-related activity, including shift claims, logs, incidents, and reports entered into the Shift Handover system.</li>
    <li>Login credentials including username and securely hashed passwords.</li>
</ul>

<h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
<p>Your information is used to:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Authenticate users and manage access rights within the system.</li>
    <li>Record and track shift activities, incidents, accidents, and manpower counts.</li>
    <li>Generate reports for operational and compliance purposes.</li>
    <li>Improve service quality and ensure the safety and efficiency of airport operations.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Information Sharing</h2>
<p>
    We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal information to third parties.
    Information may be shared internally within BAS Airport Company strictly for operational, administrative, and security purposes.
</p>

<h2>Data Security</h2>
<p>
    We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect the information we collect and store against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction.
    Passwords are securely hashed and sensitive data is stored in secure servers with restricted access.
</p>

<h2>Your Responsibilities</h2>
<p>
    Users are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of their login credentials and are encouraged to follow good security practices, such as choosing strong passwords and logging out after using the system.
</p>

<h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
<p>
    We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or for other operational, legal, or regulatory reasons.
    We encourage you to review this page periodically for any updates.
</p>

<h2>Contact Us</h2>
<p>
    If you have any questions or concerns regarding this Privacy Policy or the handling of your information, please contact the BAS IT Department.
</p>
